%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20bought%20my%20first%20house%20in%20rural%20Scotland%20at%2022.%20Housing%20is%20affordable%20in%20the%20countryside%20and%20I%20love%20it%20here.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222736%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Painting%20of%20Glen%20Coe%2C%20a%20Scottish%20mountain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e6f5acce7f1785b2e63a0e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221824%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESimran%20Kaur%20loves%20countryside%20living%20in%20Kilmarnock%2C%20Scotland%2C%20where%20she%20moved%20after%20studying%20in%20Glasgow%20for%20four%20years.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Mulligan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESimran%20Kaur%20is%20a%2022-year-old%20tax%20associate%20at%20PwC%20who%20moved%20from%20India%20to%20Scotland%20when%20she%20was%2018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20bought%20a%20house%20in%20the%20Scottish%20countryside%20after%20graduating%20from%20university%20in%20Glasgow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKaur%20worked%20alongside%20her%20studies%20and%20saved%20to%20be%20able%20to%20put%20a%20deposit%20down%20on%20her%20first%20house.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Simran%20Kaur%2C%20a%2022%20year-old%20tax%20associate%20living%20in%20Kilmarnock%2C%20Scotland.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20to%20Scotland%20from%20Punjab%2C%20North%20India%2C%20in%202019.%20I%20was%2018%20years%20old%20and%20stayed%20with%20my%20relatives%20while%20I%20studied%20accountancy%20at%20Glasgow%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20moved%20from%20Punjab%2C%20I%20worried%20about%20making%20friends%20and%20communicating%20across%20the%20language%20barrier.%20But%20thankfully%2C%20that%20worry%20eased%20very%20early%20on.%20No%20one%20laughed%20at%20my%20accent%20or%20how%20I%20dressed%20which%20gave%20me%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20having%20issues%20with%20which%20side%20of%20the%20road%20to%20get%20buses%20from%2C%20but%20strangers%20would%20often%20help.%20Scottish%20friendliness%20is%20one%20of%20the%20perks%20of%20living%20here.%20The%20weather%20is%20debatable%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20came%20to%20Scotland%20without%20a%20set%20plan%20for%20my%20future.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%20I've%20graduated%2C%20landed%20a%20good%20job%20at%20an%20internationally%20renowned%20firm%20and%20bought%20my%20first%20house%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20and%20a%20house%20at%20the%20same%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20during%20my%20final%20year%20and%20around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20was%20talk%20of%20my%20sister%20joining%20me%20to%20pursue%20her%20further%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20nice%20for%20us%20to%20rent%20a%20place%20together%20in%20Glasgow%2C%20but%20my%20family%20suggested%20it%20would%20be%20worth%20looking%20at%20the%20mortgage%20possibilities%20for%20a%20foreigner.%20So%2C%20I%20started%20looking%20into%20both%20my%20home%20and%20job%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20and%20living%20with%20relatives%20helped%20me%20save%20money%20during%20my%20studies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20and%20saving%20during%20my%20university%20years%20meant%20I%20had%20enough%20savings%20to%20consider%20buying%20a%20house.%20I%20worked%2020%20hours%20a%20week%20during%20term%20time%2C%20the%20legal%20limit%20for%20students%20on%20a%20study%20visa%2C%20and%2040%20hours%20during%20holidays.%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20Chinese%20restaurant%20at%20one%20point%20and%20McDonald's%2C%20where%20I%20got%20promoted%20to%20be%20a%20trainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20fourth%20and%20final%20year%2C%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20of%20my%20next%20steps%2C%20so%20I%20stopped%20spending%20money%20on%20things%20I%20didn't%20need%2C%20like%20clothes%2C%20and%20started%20saving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20student%2C%20I%20was%20exempt%20from%20paying%20council%20tax%20and%20didn't%20have%20to%20spend%20money%20on%20rent%20because%20I%20lived%20with%20relatives.%20This%20helped%20me%20save.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20graduated%2C%20I%20had%20saved%20%C2%A310%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20application%20process%20for%20accountancy%20firms%20was%20tough%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20to%20three%20companies%2C%20including%20Ernst%20and%20Young%20and%20PWC%2C%20and%20it%20took%20around%20three%20months%20to%20pass%20all%20the%20different%20tests.%20The%20process%20was%20lengthy%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20find%20a%20company%20willing%20to%20sponsor%20me%2C%20but%20I%20progressed%20with%20PWC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interview%20was%20difficult%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0I%20had%20to%20show%20my%20knowledge%20of%20the%20field%2C%20confidence%2C%20and%20friendliness.%20But%20it%20was%20worth%20it.%20I%20landed%20my%20role%20as%20a%20tax%20associate%20and%20started%20last%20September%20on%20a%20three-year%20contract%20right%20out%20of%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20needed%20a%20loan%20to%20buy%20my%20first%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20quite%20challenging%20to%20find%20a%20bank%20that%20would%20lend%20to%20me%20since%20I%20wasn't%20a%20UK%20citizen%2C%20but%20other%20than%20that%2C%20buying%20the%20house%20as%20a%20first-time%20buyer%20was%20a%20simple%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hired%20a%20lawyer%20to%20help%20with%20the%20process.%20Given%20how%20much%20work%20she%20did%2C%20I%20think%20her%20fee%20was%20reasonable%2C%20and%20I%20paid%20her%20after%20I%20was%20two%20months%20into%20my%20job%2C%20which%20was%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20looking%20for%20an%20area%20where%20I%20could%20reach%20my%20work%20and%20relatives%20easily.%20My%20search%20took%20me%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMotherwell%2C%20Prestwick%2C%20and%20Glasgow%2C%20which%20was%20particularly%20expensive.%20Ultimately%2C%20I%20found%20a%20lovely%20three-bedroom%20house%20in%20Kilmarnock%2C%20which%20my%20sister%20and%20I%20moved%20into%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20choose%20Kilmarnock%20because%20house%20prices%20are%20affordable%2C%20and%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20commute%20to%20work%20and%20reach%20my%20relatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'd%20found%20a%20bank%2C%20I%20could%20cover%2090%25%20with%20the%20mortgage%20and%2010%25%20through%20the%20deposit.%20The%20total%20deposit%20was%20around%20%C2%A312%2C000.%20I%20contributed%209%25%20of%20the%20deposit%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20gave%20the%20final%201%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20love%20living%20in%20the%20Scottish%20countryside%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20I'll%20stay%20forever%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20glad%20I%20worked%20and%20saved%20during%20university%20because%20I%20love%20where%20I%20live%20now%20and%20don't%20feel%20like%20I%20missed%20out%20on%20anything.%20I'm%20more%20of%20a%20countryside%20person%20and%20enjoy%20seeing%20the%20mountains%20from%20my%20window%20when%20I%20wake%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20more%20money%2C%20I%20would%20move%20to%20Loch%20Lomond%2C%20in%20southern%20Scotland%2C%20which%20has%20more%20beautiful%20scenery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20sure%20what%20I%20will%20do%20after%20my%20contract%20finishes%20and%20whether%20a%20move%20to%20another%20country%20is%20on%20the%20horizon.%20But%20I%20would%20highly%20recommend%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20in%20Scotland%2C%20especially%20the%20countryside%20%E2%80%94%20it%20has%20a%20quieter%20pace%20of%20life%20than%20in%20Glasgow%2C%20which%20I%20prefer%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20good%20balance%20between%20work%20and%20your%20social%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20possible%20to%20make%20a%20life%20for%20yourself%20here%20with%20proper%20planning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20to%20a%20different%20country%20is%20a%20huge%20decision%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20costly%2C%20so%20it's%20good%20to%20have%20some%20money%20before%20moving%20as%20it%20may%20take%20a%20few%20months%20to%20find%20a%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20spending%20on%20things%20you%20don't%20need%2C%20it's%20better%20to%20save.%20You%20have%20to%20ask%20yourself%20questions%20like%20what%20you%20need%20in%20your%20life%20and%20what%20you%20want%20to%20achieve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20lucky%20as%20an%20international%20student%20to%20have%20relatives%20to%20stay%20with%2C%20but%20for%20those%20who%20don't%20have%20that%20option%2C%20it's%20still%20possible%20to%20make%20a%20life%20for%20yourself%20in%20Scotland.%20It%20just%20requires%20proper%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-bought-my-first-house-22-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709718881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e71162ce7f1785b2e63d7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-bought-my-first-house-22-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20moving%20from%20India%20to%20Scotland%20for%20university%2C%20Simran%20Kaur%20decided%20to%20settle%20in%20the%20countryside%20and%20bought%20her%20first%20house%20at%2022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Gouri%20Sharma)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-bought-my-first-house-22-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Free%20Movement%20Regime%20Hasn%E2%80%99t%20Been%20Implemented%20Yet%2C%20Says%20Manipur%20CM%20Biren%20Singh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20124144%2FF1SovOrXoAA5F5U.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nearly%20a%20month%20after%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20announcement%20on%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funion-govts-decision-to-end-free-movement-with-myanmar-raises-concerns-in-nagaland%5C%22%3Escrapping%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Free%20Movement%20Regime%20(FMR)%20with%20Myanmar%2C%20Manipur%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20told%20the%20state%20assembly%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20has%20not%20been%20scrapped%20yet.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%208%2C%20Shah%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-amit-shah-kuki-zo-myanmar%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2003884%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMinistry%2520of%2520Home%2520Affairs%2520(MHA%2CNorth%2520Eastern%2520States%2520bordering%2520Myanmar%5C%22%3Ethat%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20to%20end%20the%20bilateral%20understanding%20with%20the%20neighbouring%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20MEA%20has%20thus%20far%20not%20issued%20any%20formal%20statement%20on%20the%20MHA%E2%80%99s%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%204%2C%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20Winter%20Session%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%2C%20Biren%20Singh%20said%20the%20FMR%20has%20not%20been%20scrapped%20yet.%20%E2%80%9CNonetheless%2C%20the%20state%20government%20has%20been%20suspending%20the%20FMR%20for%20every%20six%20months%20with%20due%20consent%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesangaiexpress.com%2FEncyc%2F2024%2F3%2F6%2FBy-Our-Staff-ReporterIMPHAL-Mar-5-Even-though-the-Ministry-of-Home-Affairs-has-written-to-the-Ministry-of.html%5C%22%3Ehe%20said.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20reply%20to%20a%20question%20by%20MLA%20and%20state%20Congress%20chief%20Meghachandra%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Manipur%20state%20administration%20had%20suspended%20the%20FMR%20with%20Myanmar%20since%202021%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20arrangement%20has%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20latest%20notification%20for%20suspension%20of%20FMR%20was%20issued%20on%20February%2016%20this%20year.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20issue%20an%20order%20whereby%20FMR%20would%20be%20scrapped%20totally%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20chief%20minister%20told%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20referring%20to%20some%20recent%20media%20reports%20about%20the%20arrest%20of%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20immigrants%20from%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D%20in%20Manipur%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20suspension%20of%20the%20FMR%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20said%20that%20citizens%20of%20the%20two%20countries%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20move%20across%20the%20border%20if%20they%20are%20permitted%20by%20authorities%20of%20both%20the%20countries%20even%20though%20FMR%20has%20been%20suspended.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20been%20a%20longstanding%20demand%20from%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20Meitei%20community%20to%20fence%20the%20international%20border%20the%20northeastern%20state%20shares%20with%20Myanmar%2C%20citing%20the%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%98illegal%20immigrants%E2%80%99%20entering%20the%20Indian%20state%20through%20it%2C%20their%20last%20ten-month-long%20ethnic%20strife%20with%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Kuki%20community%20has%20also%20seen%20a%20vociferous%20demand%20to%20not%20only%20fence%20the%20border%20but%20also%20scrap%20the%20FMR%20understanding%20too%2C%20as%20per%20which%20people%20residing%20on%20both%20sides%20can%20cross%20the%20international%20border%20up%20to%2016%20kilometres%20without%20passport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Meitei%20civil%20society%20groups%20have%20been%20alleging%20that%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20immigrants%E2%80%9D%20have%20intruded%20into%20the%20border%20areas%20populated%20by%20the%20Kuki%20community%2C%20who%20share%20kinship%20with%20those%20across%20the%20international%20boundary%2C%20thereby%20posing%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20population%20of%20the%20majority%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20scrap%20India%E2%80%99s%20FMR%20with%20Myanmar%20has%20been%20welcomed%20by%20the%20majority%20Meitei%20population%20of%20Manipur%2C%20it%20has%20been%20vehemently%20opposed%20not%20only%20by%20the%20Kukis%20of%20the%20state%20but%20also%20by%20the%20Mizos%20and%20Nagas%20across%20Manipur%2C%20Mizoram%20and%20Nagaland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Mizoram%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fguwahati%2Fnagaland-joins-mizoram-in-opposing-suspension-of-fmr%2Farticleshow%2F108153023.cms%5C%22%3ENagaland%3C%2Fa%3E%20assemblies%20have%20passed%20resolutions%20to%20oppose%20the%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20citing%20kinship%20with%20the%20people%20across%20the%20international%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMizoram%20chief%20minister%20Lalduhoma%20has%20recently%20met%20Shah%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%20the%20matter.%20The%20Naga%20Students%E2%80%99%20Federation%20has%20written%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20to%20intervene%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%201%2C643-km-long%20India-Myanmar%20border%2C%20398%20km%20runs%20along%20Manipur%2C%20215%20km%20along%20Nagaland%2C%20520%20km%20along%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20and%20520%20km%20along%20Mizoram.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709718348000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20124144%2FF1SovOrXoAA5F5U.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffree-movement-regime-hasnt-been-implemented-yet-says-manipur-cm-biren-singh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20reply%20to%20a%20question%20by%20MLA%20and%20state%20Congress%20chief%20Meghachandra%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20said%20that%20the%20Manipur%20state%20administration%20had%20suspended%20the%20FMR%20with%20Myanmar%20since%202021%20due%20to%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20arrangement%20is%20still%20continuing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2